| (2.4) |  | u(t,x)=\int\_{\mathbb{R}}e^{ix\lambda}E\_{\beta}(-\mu|\lambda|^{\alpha}(1+|% \lambda|^{2})^{\gamma/2}t^{\beta})Z(d\lambda), |  |

where E\_{\beta}(\cdot) is the Mittag-Leffler function defined as

|  |  |  |
| --- | --- | --- |
|  | E\_{\beta}(s):=\sum\_{k=0}^{\infty}\frac{s^{k}}{\Gamma(1+\beta k)},\qquad s\in% \mathbb{R},\ 0<\beta<1. |  |

For the negative values of its argument, it satisfies the inequality

|  |  |  |  |
